claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table listing contraindications and precautions for different types of 2022–23 influenza vaccines (egg-based IIVs and LAIV4, cell culture–based ccIIV4, and recombinant RIV4) in individuals with previous severe allergic reactions to various vaccines The table addresses allergy-related contraindications and precautions for influenza vaccines and does not mention mutations during production or their impact on vaccine effectiveness, and thus does not support the claim
